cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a method for automatically constructing security argument graphs. It may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses the use of formalisms to manage risk and maintain documentation throughout the system lifecycle. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of logical relationships and templates, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the prototype software tool mentioned in the paper suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
